alifornia Street<br>San Francisco, CA 94108<br>phone: (1) 415-989-3500<br>fax: (1) 415-986-8195<br><B>Rates: $170 U.S. single/double   (Plus 14% tax)</B></blockquote><P>Hotel reservation cut-off date for this hotel at this rate is 15 July 1999. A reservation deposit of first night's room and tax charges will be required at time of reservation</P><P>Low-priced accommodation alternative for students or others on a tight budget are the San Francisco area hostels. Listed below are a few hostels in the area. Fees vary, but average about $20/night.<P><B>Hostelling International</B> San Francisco Union Square 312 Mason Street San Francisco, CA 94102 415-788-5604<P><B>European Guest House</B> 761 Minna St. San Francisco, CA 94103-2707 415-861-6634</p></td>	<td><img src="ico_images/fishmap.gif" alt="map" width="150" height="196" border="0" hspace="4" vspace="4"></td></tr></table><h3>Fairmont Hotel San Francisco</h3><img src="ico_images/fairmontphoto.gif" alt="photo of hotel" width="200" height="142" hspace="4" vspace="4" border="0" align="right"><P>Renowned the world over, the Fairmont Hotel in San Francisco offers an unmatched blend of historic elegance and 21<SUP>st</SUP>-century service. Built in 1907, The Fairmont is centrally located atop San Francisco's prestigious Nob Hill - just a cable car ride from Fisherman's Wharf, Chinatown, Union Square, and the Financial District. <P>The hotel provides 600 deluxe guest rooms with each room featuring: multiple telephones and private voice-mail messaging, computer dataport, remote controlled color TV with on-command video, both goose-down and hypoallergenic foam pillows are available, comforters in every room, oversized bath towels, handmilled soaps, shampoos, conditioner, and lotions, hair dryer, in-room refreshment center, and electric shoe polisher.<P>World-class dining is a unique part of The Fairmont experience. Their four distinctive restaurants each offer expertly prepared cuisine in comfortable settings. Guests may enjoy tropical refreshments in the exotic Tonga Restaurant, with its indoor rainstorms and live dance band. In the Bella Voce, superb Italian cuisine is served each evening by professional singers performing favorites from Broadway, opera, and more. Sample special grilled cuisine at Masons, and buffet dining with spectacular views in the Crown Restaurant. To keep up with your fitness routine, you can work out at the Nob Hill Club, staffed with fitness trainers, massage therapists, and aerobics instructors. The club offers complete facilities plus luxurious private spas for men and women.<P>The hotel boasts a multilingual staff, 24-hour concierges, executive business center, complimentary overnight shoe shine, foreign currency exchange, car rental, national and international FAX, safety deposit boxes, pharmacy, beauty salon, and baby sitters.</td></tr></table><img src="ico_images/hotelmap.gif" alt="map" width="499" height="1060" hspace="4" vspace="4" border="0"><hr size="5"><p align="center"><font size="-1" face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="ico99_sched.html">Meeting Schedule</a> |<a href="3749.html">Conference Program</a> |<a href="geninfo.html">General Information</a> |<a href="travel.html">Travel</a> |<a href="ico99_regform.html">Registration Form</a> |<a href="banquet.html">Banquet</a> |<a href="leisure.html">Leisure Time</a></font></p><hr size=5><H3 align="center">For further information please contact:</H3><center><table cellpadding="2"><tr><th><a href="http://www.ico-optics.org"><img src="ico_images/ICOlogo.gif" alt="ICO - CIO" width="98" height="98" border="0" hspace="5" vspace="5"></a></th><th><a href="http://www.spie.org"><img src="http://www.spie.org/web/gifs/meeting_gifs/spielogo.gif" alt="SPIE - The International Society for Optical Engineering" width="173" height="36" border="0" hspace="14" vspace="4"></a></th></tr></table><p align="CENTER"><font size=-1>&copy; 1999 <a href="http://w